-- South African Stocks: AngloGold, Harmony, Impala, Lonmin Move
-- B y   S t e p h e n   G u n n i o n
-- 2012-01-04T08:27:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-04/south-african-stocks-anglogold-harmony-impala-lonmin-move.html
The  FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index (JALSH) 
gained 0.6 percent to 32,956.47 by 10:16 a.m. in Johannesburg,
its highest intra-day level in almost a month.  The following are among the active equities in the South
African market today. Stock symbols follow company names.  AngloGold Ashanti Ltd. (ANG)  , Africa’s biggest producer
of the metal, increased for a third day, adding 0.5 percent to
351.89 rand. Gold rose as much as 0.6 percent to $1,613.26 an
ounce, a fourth day of advances, reversing an earlier decline.  Harmony Gold Mining Co. (HAR)  ,  South Africa ’s third-
largest gold producer, gained 1.3 percent to 97.88 rand.  Impala Platinum Holdings Ltd. (IMP)  , the second-biggest
producer of the metal, advanced for a third day, adding 0.7
percent to 170.77 rand. Platinum gained as much as 0.6 percent
to $1,434.50 an ounce, a third day of rises.  Lonmin Plc (LMI)  , the third-biggest platinum miner,
climbed 1.4 percent to 128.51 rand.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Stephen Gunnion in Johannesburg at 
